<title>USA: Microsoft unveils Marble Internet software.</title>
<headline>Microsoft unveils Marble Internet software.</headline>
<dateline>REDMOND, Wash. 1997-03-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Microsoft Corp on Wednesday unveiled its new Internet platform, called Marble, aimed at financial institutions that want to make their sites on the World Wide Web more secure.</p>
<p>Marble will help developers create Web sites that allow customers to view statements, transfer funds and pay bills online. The platform is based on an open systems approach to financial software programming known as the Open Financial Exchange specification.</p>
